# E-Commerce Project Standards

Stack: **Next.js 14+ App Router**, **TypeScript (strict)**, **Supabase** (database/auth/storage), **Tailwind CSS**, **Razorpay**, **react-hook-form + zod**.

## TypeScript

- Use TypeScript everywhere — no `.js` source files.
- Keep `strict: true` in `tsconfig.json`; do not weaken compiler options.
- Prefer explicit types for public APIs, props, and database rows. Avoid `any`.

## Next.js App Router

- Use the `app/` directory only — **never** create a `pages/` directory.
- Default to **Server Components**; add `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, browser APIs, interactivity).
- Route Handlers live in `app/api/**/route.ts`.
- Use `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, and `not-found.tsx` where appropriate.

## Supabase Client Usage

```typescript
// ✅ Server Component or Route Handler
import { createServerClient } from "@/lib/supabase/server";

// ✅ Client Component
import { createBrowserClient } from "@/lib/supabase/client";
```

- **Server Components / Route Handlers**: use the server client from `/lib/supabase/server`.
- **Client Components**: use the browser client from `/lib/supabase/client` only.
- Never import the browser client in server code or the server client in client components.

## Database Access

- **All** database reads/writes go through `/lib/supabase` or `/lib/db` — never in components or pages.
- Components call server actions, route handlers, or lib functions; they do not run queries directly.
- Never use raw SQL in UI layers. Encapsulate Supabase queries in named lib functions.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — query in a component
const { data } = await supabase.from("products").select("*");

// ✅ GOOD — lib function consumed by Server Component
import { getProducts } from "@/lib/db/products";
const products = await getProducts();
```

## Types

- Every new Supabase table needs a matching TypeScript type in `/types` (e.g. `/types/product.ts`).
- Export row, insert, and update types where applicable. Keep types in sync with schema migrations.

## Styling (Tailwind)

- Use **Tailwind utility classes** for all styling.
- No inline `style={{}}` props. No CSS Modules. No separate `.css` files for component styles (global `globals.css` for base/theme tokens only).

## Forms & Validation

- Use **react-hook-form** with **zod** schemas via `@hookform/resolvers/zod`.
- Define schemas in `/lib/validations` or colocated with the feature; reuse schemas on client and server where possible.
- Validate on the server for mutations even when client validation exists.

## Naming Conventions

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Files & folders | kebab-case | `product-card.tsx`, `order-summary/` |
| React components | PascalCase | `ProductCard`, `OrderSummary` |
| Functions & variables | camelCase | `getOrderById`, `cartItems` |
| Types & interfaces | PascalCase | `Product`, `OrderStatus` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_CART_QUANTITY` |

## Payments (Razorpay)

- Keep Razorpay secret keys server-side only (env vars, Route Handlers, server actions).
- Client receives only the public key and order/session details needed to open checkout.
- Verify payment signatures on the server before updating order status.

## File Organization

```
app/           # routes, layouts, Server Components
components/    # shared UI (kebab-case files, PascalCase exports)
lib/
  supabase/    # client factories (server.ts, client.ts)
  db/          # database query functions
  validations/ # zod schemas
types/         # database & domain types
```
